{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect function calls in steady state RWP mobility model\n\n### Summary\nThe steady state Random Waypoint (RWP) mobility model in the OMG module was not behaving as expected during node updates. Nodes were not following the steady state RWP movement patterns and instead exhibited regular RWP behavior.\n\nAfter investigation, the issue was found in the `update_steadystaterwp_nodes()` function in `openair2/UTIL/OMG/steadystaterwp.c`. The function was incorrectly calling regular RWP functions (`sleep_rwp_node` and `move_rwp_node`) instead of the steady state RWP equivalents (`sleep_steadystaterwp_node` and `move_steadystaterwp_node`).\n\nThis caused nodes to use the regular RWP mobility logic during updates, even though they were initialized with steady state RWP parameters. The fix ensures that the steady state RWP functions are called consistently throughout the node lifecycle.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/UTIL/OMG/steadystaterwp.c`: \n  - Line 514: Changed `sleep_rwp_node(tmp->pair, cur_time)` to `sleep_steadystaterwp_node(tmp->pair, cur_time)`\n  - Line 516: Changed `move_rwp_node(tmp->pair, cur_time)` to `move_steadystaterwp_node(tmp->pair, cur_time)`\n  - Line 528: Changed `sleep_rwp_node(tmp->pair, cur_time)` to `sleep_steadystaterwp_node(tmp->pair, cur_time)`\n  - Line 530: Changed `move_rwp_node(tmp->pair, cur_time)` to `move_steadystaterwp_node(tmp->pair, cur_time)`\n\n"
}